cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.GR 

This paper is about image registration, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The method proposed involves a deep encoder-decoder network, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The network is trained to predict deformation parameters based on image appearance, which involves learning a mapping between input and output data (cs.AI). The paper also discusses computational efficiency, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT), and includes visualizations of the results, which is a common practice in computer graphics (cs.GR).
